# 02 - Frontend Setup (React)

This guide outlines the steps to set up the React frontend for the Expense Tracker app.

---

## 📁 Navigate to client folder

```bash
cd expense-tracker/client
```

## ⚙️ Initialize React app

```bash
npx create-react-app .
```

## 📦 Install required packages

```bash
npm install axios react-router-dom
```

## 🗃️ Folder Suggestions

```
client/
├── src/
│   ├── components/      # Reusable UI components
│   ├── pages/           # Auth, Dashboard pages
│   ├── context/         # Global state (e.g., AuthContext)
│   ├── hooks/           # Custom hooks (useAuth, etc.)
│   ├── services/        # API handlers (axios)
│   ├── App.js
│   └── index.js
```

## 🚀 Start React App

```bash
npm start
```

The React app runs at: [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000)

You’re ready to begin building components!
